member.remarks:
This convenience function creates the following message and sends it to 'rex' on the remote node:
{ Self, { call, Mod, Fun, Args, user }}
Note that this method has unpredicatble results if the remote node is not an Erlang node

Normally this method should be used in conjunction with
, when is is necessary to insert data into
the stream before it is known what the actual value should be.
For example:


int pos = s.Position;
s.Write4BE(0); // make space for length data,
// but final value is not yet known

[ ...more write statements...]

// later... when we know the length value
s.Poke4BE(pos, length);

member.example:
